Diagnosis. This species is distinguished from its congeners by the medially very narrow face, as narrow as width of an adjacent ommatidium at narrowest point, the entirely brown metathoracic tibia, and R1 reaching C at or distal to R5 joining C (
Fig. 36
).

Distribution. Brazil, Costa Rica, Panama, Peru, Trinidad and Tobago, Venezuela (
Fig. 37
). Biodiversity hotspot/high-biodiversity wilderness area: Mesoamerica/Amazonia (
Fig. 37
).
